#~ msgid ""
#~ "Compare the <literal>netstat</literal> results with those of a thorough "
#~ "port scan done from outside your host. An excellent program for this job "
#~ "is <literal>nmap</literal>, which not only checks out the ports of your "
#~ "machine, but also draws some conclusions as to which services are waiting "
#~ "behind them. However, port scanning may be interpreted as an aggressive "
#~ "act, so do not do this on a host without the explicit approval of the "
#~ "administrator. Finally, remember that it is important not only to scan "
#~ "TCP ports, but also UDP ports (options <option>-sS</option> and <option>-"
#~ "sU</option>)."
